data.description: Private estate on 20 +/- acres. This is property is an outdoorsman's dream. Meticulously maintained log home built to last. Adjoins Mark Twain National Forest and has hunting rights. Large windows for natural light that overlooks the back patio and inground pool. 5 spacious bedrooms and 5 bathrooms. Multiple areas perfect for entertaining your friends and family. Beautiful craftsmanship with wood beams and tongue and groove ceilings. Stately wood burning, stone fireplace for those cool cozy evenings. Beautiful kitchen design with Corian countertops and ample storage. Game/billiard room downstairs in the walkout basement.  Dual fuel heat and air. New deck last year, reinforced for the hot tub. The property has a spring fed creek deep enough to swim in. 3 car oversized attached garage and a detached 24x32 shop/garage. Conveniently located 20 minutes East of Ozark and 30 minutes to Springfield. This is a one-of-a-kind property with too many features to mention, you have to see this one in person.
